<TITLE> 3 to die in Kurigram for killing mother </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Kurigram, Sept 16 (bdnews24.com) - A Kurigram court Sunday sentenced three sons to death for killing their mother. Additional district and sessions judge Farzana Begum delivered the verdict in a case filed by father Asgar Ali Sufi. On June 15, 2006, Abdul Latif, 35, Abdul Hye, 32, and Abdus Sobhan, 28, knifed their parents in desperation to grab the paternal property and mother Jamela Khatun died on the spot. According case proceedings, Sufi of Sukdevkundu village under Gunaigachh union of Ulipur upazila separated his three sons for their rowdiness and built separate house for them. The three brothers, who had been eyeing their father's property, asked for Tk 20,000. Furious on being refused, they indiscriminately stabbed their parents with sharp knives. The mother died instantly and the father was rushed by neighbours to hispital. They handed the three brothers in to the police. On June 16, 2006 Asgar Ali filed a murder case with Ulipur Police Station against the three sons. bdnews2
